Jump Search in Python

Jump search is a searching algorithm for sorted arrays that works by jumping 
ahead by fixed steps and then performing a linear search in the identified block.

Time Complexity
Best case: O(1) - target is the first element
Average case: O(√n) - optimal step size
Worst case: O(√n) - when the target is at the end

Space Complexity: O(1)


import math
def jump_search(arr, target):
    n = len(arr)
    
    if n == 0:
        return -1

    step = int(math.sqrt(n))
    prev = 0
    
    while arr[min(step, n) - 1] < target:
        prev = step
        step += int(math.sqrt(n))
        
        if prev >= n:
            return -1
    
    for i in range(prev, min(step, n)):
        if arr[i] == target:
            return i
  
        if arr[i] > target:
            break
    
    return -1
    
